<FONT size=4 color=#000000>Superiors</STRONG><BR>
<BR>
   <I>Section Chief Scott Blevins</I> (Charles Cioffi) is with the Violent Crimes<BR>
Section of the Bureau. Blevins is responsable for assigning Scully to be<BR>
Mulder's partner.<BR>
<BR>
   <I>Section Chief Joseph McGrath</I> (Frederick Coffin) is with the Office of<BR>
Professional Responsibility and seems determined to have Mulder fired and<BR>
<I>The X-Files</I> shut down.<BR>
<BR>
  <I> Assistant Director Walter Sergei Skinner</I> (Mitch Pileggi) is one of the<BR>
Bureau higher-ups reading Scully's reports. Skinner, now seperated from his<BR>
wife, Sharon, is an Ex-Marine, who volunteered for service at the age of 18.<BR>
He claims to have experienced a near-death experience during his service<BR>
there. He has warned Scully and Mulder that their unorthodox methods of<BR>
investigation may have dire consequences, and followed through by shutting<BR>
down <I>The X-Files</I> division at an order from the highest levels of<BR>
government. Reopened <I>The X-Files</I> in an attempt to save Scully's life<BR>
(See  <A HREF="2.8.html">One Breath</A>).<BR>
   He receives frequent visits from the  <A HREF="RCs.html">Cigarette Smoking Man</A>, Skinner<BR>
and, although appears to dislike him, his exact relationship with him is<BR>
unknown.<BR>
